1. Cmd+Shift+Space opens a small frameless floating window from any app on macOS
  2. Window contains auto-focused title input and destination dropdown (My Day + all projects)
  3. My Day is selected by default in the destination dropdown
  4. Enter creates the task and closes the window
  5. Escape closes the window without creating a task
  6. Task is created with default status, correct project, and respects new task position setting
  7. When My Day is selected, task has is_in_my_day: 1
  8. Main window task list refreshes silently after quick-add without being shown or focused
  9. Shortcut is customizable in Settings > General via a Record button
  10. Known macOS shortcuts are blocked with a message naming the specific macOS feature
  11. Unknown shortcut conflicts warn and ask to overwrite
  12. Shortcut persists across app restarts (saved in settings)
  13. Closing the main window hides it — app stays alive, shortcut stays registered
  14. Clicking dock icon re-opens the main window
  15. Cmd+Q fully quits the app and unregisters the shortcut
  16. Shortcut does nothing if user is not logged in
  17. Quick-add window matches the current app theme